{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 18:56:52.678479", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submitted findings:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- Faulty device(s): server_access_router\n- Root cause chosen: ospf_area_misconfiguration\n\nNotes:\n- The diagnosis supports that the server_access_router is advertising the 10.200.0.0/24 server subnet into OSPF (network statement in FRR) and thus exposing backend web servers directly to host subnets. The core routers are correctly propagating these routes. The underlying issue is lack of segmentation/ACLs/route filtering (reported as an OSPF advertisement/configuration problem), not a network outage.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2440, "output_tokens": 129, "total_tokens": 2569, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
